humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report indicates that 22/22 lymph nodes are positive for metastasis (Axillares 22/22). This corresponds to N3 stage based on New Rule 13: N3 indicates metastases in 4 or more axillary lymph nodes.

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The patient has 22/22 positive lymph nodes (Axillares 22/22) in the axillary region, which corresponds to an N3 stage according to the TNM staging system for cancer. The number of positive lymph nodes is significantly higher than the threshold for N1 and N2 stages, making N3 the appropriate stage for this patient.
